01:35.617 --> 01:37.488
♪ NO, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.619 --> 01:40.970
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.886
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:47.063
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:01.991 --> 02:05.560
[BEACH GOERS CHATTERING
IN BACKGROUND]

02:28.322 --> 02:29.453
-MATT: YOU GOT THE TIME?

02:30.237 --> 02:31.412
-10:20.

02:33.979 --> 02:35.677
-YOU DIDN'T EVEN
LOOK AT YOUR WATCH.

02:36.286 --> 02:39.463
-THE MERMAID. SHE SWIMS
EVERY MORNING AT 10.

02:39.985 --> 02:41.639
AND EVERY AFTERNOON AT 5.

02:42.162 --> 02:43.598
TAKES HER EXACTLY 20 MINUTES

02:43.728 --> 02:45.208
TO SWIM AROUND
THAT BUOY AND BACK.

02:45.730 --> 02:48.298
NOT 19, NOT 21.

02:50.082 --> 02:51.432
-YOU'RE PUTTING ME ON, RIGHT?

02:51.562 --> 02:53.912
-SHE'LL KNOCK THE WATER
OUT OF HER LEFT EAR.

02:55.087 --> 02:57.002
SHE'LL SHAKE HER HEAD AROUND,

02:58.439 --> 03:01.572
AND SHE'LL RUN STRAIGHT
BACK INTO HER BEACH HOUSE,

03:01.703 --> 03:05.185
NOT TO RETURN 'TIL
HER AFTERNOON SWIM.

03:13.193 --> 03:14.716
-YOU'RE AMAZING.

03:14.846 --> 03:16.674
-MATT, YOU'VE
GOTTA BE OBSERVANT.

03:16.805 --> 03:18.937
GOTTA KNOW WHAT PEOPLE
ARE DOING ON YOUR BEACH.

03:19.068 --> 03:20.461
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ON MY BEACH?

03:20.591 --> 03:22.550
-OH, UM, THEY NEED
YOU AT HEADQUARTERS.

03:22.680 --> 03:23.551
I'M HERE TO RELIEVE YOU.

03:23.681 --> 03:24.900
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

03:25.553 --> 03:28.208
-I DON'T KNOW, BUT STEPHANIE
SEEMED INTENSE.

03:29.600 --> 03:31.472
-STEPHANIE'S BEEN
INTENSE EVER SINCE RILEY

03:31.602 --> 03:33.430
ASKED HER TO SAIL AROUND
THE WORLD WITH HIM.

03:33.952 --> 03:35.345
-YOU THINK SHE'LL DO IT?

03:35.476 --> 03:37.347
-NEVER. SHE'LL THINK
ABOUT IT, DEBATE IT,

03:37.478 --> 03:40.220
WEIGH THE PROS AND CONS,
AND THEN PLAY IT SAFE.

03:42.047 --> 03:43.614
KEEP AN EYE ON THOSE
TOURISTS, WILL YA?

03:43.745 --> 03:45.442
THEY HAVE NO IDEA WHAT THEY'RE
DOING IN THE WATER,

03:45.573 --> 03:47.314
AND I DON'T THINK THEY
SPEAK VERY GOOD ENGLISH.

03:55.539 --> 03:57.498
[TRUCK ENGINE CRANKS]

03:59.717 --> 04:01.023
[PEOPLE CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

04:02.851 --> 04:04.026
-WHAT'S THE FBI DOIN' HERE?

04:04.156 --> 04:05.245
-THEY WANT ONE OF THEIR AGENTS

04:05.375 --> 04:06.637
TO GO UNDERCOVER AS A LIFEGUARD.

04:06.768 --> 04:07.943
[MITCH LAUGHS]

04:08.465 --> 04:09.684
-THEY'LL NEVER
GET AWAY WITH IT.

04:09.814 --> 04:11.555
THOSE GUYS ALL LOOK ALIKE.

04:12.295 --> 04:14.689
BAD HAIRCUTS, PALE
SKIN, DARK SUNGLASSES.

04:14.819 --> 04:17.474
OH, YOU CAN SPOT
'EM A MILE AWAY.

04:17.605 --> 04:19.259
HI. YOU NEW HERE?

04:19.389 --> 04:20.911
-YES, AS A MATTER OF FACT I AM.

04:21.043 --> 04:22.000
-WHERE YOU FROM?

04:22.130 --> 04:23.263
-ABOUT A MILE AWAY.

04:23.872 --> 04:25.874
-OH, LIEUTENANT MITCH BUCHANAN,

04:26.004 --> 04:28.572
MEET FBI SPECIAL AGENT
MORGAN CHRISTOPHER.

04:30.618 --> 04:32.924
-WELL, YOU PASSED
THE FIRST TEST.

04:33.055 --> 04:35.057
THAT'S AN EXCELLENT
UNDERCOVER LOOK.

04:35.187 --> 04:36.580
WHY DON'T WE GO IN
MY OFFICE AND DISCUSS

04:36.711 --> 04:38.408
EXACTLY WHY YOU'RE HERE?

04:39.061 --> 04:40.018
-AFTER YOU, LIEUTENANT.

04:40.149 --> 04:41.455
-NO, NO, PLEASE, AFTER YOU.

04:45.633 --> 04:47.069
[GROANS]

04:47.199 --> 04:49.941
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
ONE THING STRAIGHT.

04:50.072 --> 04:51.726
I DON'T WANNA BE IN
THIS SO-CALLED UNIFORM

04:51.856 --> 04:53.423
ANY MORE THAN YOU WANT ME IN IT.

04:53.554 --> 04:55.425
BUT, UNFORTUNATELY,

04:55.556 --> 04:57.427
I HAVE TO STAKE OUT
A HOUSE ON THE BEACH.

04:58.080 --> 04:58.994
-WHICH HOUSE?

05:02.040 --> 05:03.477
[CLEARS THROAT]

05:06.393 --> 05:07.959
ISN'T THIS NEAR YOUR TOWER?

05:11.528 --> 05:13.269
-YOU'RE STAKING
OUT THE MERMAID?

05:13.878 --> 05:16.054
-TANYA HARPSTER. WHAT
DO YOU KNOW ABOUT HER?

05:16.664 --> 05:18.318
-WELL, NOTHIN' MUCH.
SHE'S A SWIMMER.

05:18.448 --> 05:20.798
SHE SWIMS EVERY
DAY AT 10 AND AT 5.

05:20.929 --> 05:22.496
WHY, WHAT'S HER STORY?

05:23.105 --> 05:25.847
-IT'S HER BOYFRIEND'S
STORY, SONNY SCANLIN.

05:25.977 --> 05:28.066
-THE MOB BOSS?
ISN'T HE IN PRISON?

05:28.197 --> 05:30.330
-HE ESCAPED TWO DAYS AGO.

05:30.460 --> 05:33.333
WE HAVE REASON TO BELIEVE THAT
HE'LL TRY AND PICK UP TANYA

05:33.463 --> 05:34.856
BEFORE HE LEAVES THE COUNTRY.

05:35.509 --> 05:38.250
HE'S VERY INTELLIGENT,
SO IS TANYA.

05:38.990 --> 05:41.297
THEY WON'T MAKE A MOVE IF
ANYTHING LOOKS SUSPICIOUS.

05:41.428 --> 05:43.560
-WELL, IS THERE ANYTHING
I CAN DO TO HELP?

05:43.691 --> 05:45.606
-YOU ARE WINDOW DRESSING,
MR. BUCHANNON.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.913
BEST WAY YOU CAN HELP
IS BY NOT INTERFERING.

05:49.044 --> 05:52.003
WE HAVE MEN ON THE BLUFF.
I WILL BE ON THE BEACH.

05:52.134 --> 05:53.744
WE'LL START FIRST
THING TOMORROW MORNING.

05:59.010 --> 06:00.534
-HUH.
[STEPHANIE EXHALES LOUDLY]

06:02.623 --> 06:03.711
-HEY, MITCH.

06:04.668 --> 06:06.017
YOU, UH, READY?

06:06.148 --> 06:08.455
-UH, YEAH. I'LL BE
THERE IN JUST A MINUTE.

06:09.804 --> 06:11.153
HAVE A GOOD TIME
TOMORROW MORNING.

06:11.283 --> 06:12.633
-WAIT A MINUTE.
WHERE ARE YOU GONNA BE?

06:12.763 --> 06:14.112
SAILING AROUND THE
WORLD WITH RILEY?

06:17.246 --> 06:18.595
-I'M CONSIDERING IT.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.162
-YEAH, I'LL BELIEVE
IT WHEN I SEE IT.

06:20.292 --> 06:22.120
-WELL, DON'T BE SHOCKED, THEN,

06:22.251 --> 06:24.601
IF I TAKE AN EXTENDED
LEAVE OF ABSENCE.

06:24.732 --> 06:25.689
-RIGHT.

06:33.958 --> 06:35.743
WINDOW DRESSING?

06:37.135 --> 06:40.922
-IT'S TOO DANGEROUS.
THE WAVE WILL TIP YOU OVER.

06:42.010 --> 06:44.447
IF YOU TIP OVER, YOU'LL DROWN.

06:45.535 --> 06:48.756
PLEASE, SIR. YOU NEED TO
BRING THE BOAT BACK TO SHORE.

06:49.626 --> 06:50.932
-C.J.: WHAT'S WRONG?

06:51.062 --> 06:52.499
-I CAN'T MAKE THEM UNDERSTAND.

06:53.456 --> 06:55.937
-[SPEAKS JAPANESE]

07:02.378 --> 07:03.466
-YOU SPEAK JAPANESE?

07:04.032 --> 07:05.120
-[SPEAKS JAPANESE]

07:05.250 --> 07:06.382
-OH, NO.

07:09.037 --> 07:09.951
TIDE'S COMING UP.

07:10.473 --> 07:11.953
SHE SHOULDN'T BE UP THERE.

07:15.304 --> 07:17.306
[EXCLAIMS EXCITEDLY]

07:18.916 --> 07:21.136
[CAMERA CLICKS]

07:22.616 --> 07:23.965
[WAVE CRASHES]
[SCREAMS]

07:24.095 --> 07:26.663
-OH, GRETA! HELP!

07:27.272 --> 07:28.665
-HELP!
[COUGHING]

07:30.014 --> 07:31.668
-GRETA!

07:46.204 --> 07:47.597
[GASPING]

07:47.728 --> 07:49.338
[BREATHING RAPIDLY]

07:49.469 --> 07:51.253
[GASPING]

07:53.908 --> 07:56.519
-I GOT YOU. DON'T
WORRY, I GOT YOU.

07:56.650 --> 07:59.566
[SIREN WAILING]

08:02.438 --> 08:04.309
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING
IN BACKGROUND]

08:04.440 --> 08:06.486
IT'S OKAY. YOU'RE
GONNA BE ALL RIGHT.

08:06.616 --> 08:09.924
-THANK YOU, THANK YOU!
YOU SAVED ME.

08:11.882 --> 08:12.970
-GRETA!

08:13.841 --> 08:15.843
[SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

08:18.846 --> 08:20.674
[SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

08:21.196 --> 08:22.850
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:22.980 --> 08:24.982
-SEARCH ME.
THIS WHOLE DAY'S BEEN CRAZY.

08:26.375 --> 08:30.248
-I AM GRETA. WERE IT NOT
FOR YOU, I WOULD BE DEAD.

08:30.858 --> 08:32.599
-OH, I WAS JUST DOING MY JOB.

08:32.729 --> 08:34.775
-IN MY VILLAGE,
IF SOMEONE SAVES YOUR LIFE,

08:34.905 --> 08:36.211
YOU MUST RETURN THEIR GIFT.

08:36.341 --> 08:37.691
-YEAH.

08:37.821 --> 08:40.520
-[LAUGHS] THAT'S
NOT REALLY NECESSARY.

08:40.650 --> 08:42.783
-YOUR COOKING, YOUR
CLEANING, WHATEVER YOU NEED.

08:42.913 --> 08:44.698
I WILL GLADLY DO IT FOR YOU.

08:44.828 --> 08:46.090
-NO KIDDING?

08:47.744 --> 08:50.486
-SORRY. LIFEGUARD
POLICY, NO REWARDS.

08:52.749 --> 08:56.579
-C.J.'S RIGHT. THANKS, BUT
YOU DON'T OWE ME ANYTHING.

08:56.710 --> 09:00.931
-I OWE YOU MY LIFE AND
UNTIL I REPAY MY DEBT TO YOU,

09:01.062 --> 09:02.454
I AM YOURS.

09:14.510 --> 09:15.293
[DOOR BANGS]

09:15.424 --> 09:17.644
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

09:21.343 --> 09:22.605
-BACK UP THE RAMP.

09:24.172 --> 09:25.826
WE ALWAYS WATCH THE WATER.

09:26.653 --> 09:28.742
-YOU WATCH THE WATER,
I'LL WATCH THE HOUSE.

09:28.872 --> 09:30.918
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

09:32.180 --> 09:33.616
-IT'S GONNA BE A LONG DAY.

09:35.618 --> 09:38.186
I TOLD YOU, YOU'RE NOT
GONNA SEE HER UNTIL 10.

09:38.316 --> 09:42.973
-WHY DON'T YOU PLAY IN
THE SAND, MEET SOME BABES,

09:43.583 --> 09:45.410
DO WHATEVER IT IS YOU DO?

09:46.977 --> 09:50.502
-YOU SURE ARE WEARING OUT YOUR
WELCOME, AGENT CHRISTOPHER.

09:50.633 --> 09:52.417
-AND YOU AND I, WE'RE
NOT GONNA DO LUNCH,

09:52.548 --> 09:54.202
WE'RE NOT GONNA HAVE
COCKTAILS AT SUNSET.

09:55.725 --> 09:59.468
-BELIEVE ME, THE THOUGHT
NEVER CROSSED MY MIND.

10:00.077 --> 10:01.035
-REALLY?

10:01.557 --> 10:02.950
THOUGHT A BEACH BOY LIKE YOU

10:03.080 --> 10:04.429
WOULD BE A REAL
BANDIT WITH THE BABES.

10:04.560 --> 10:06.040
-WHAT IS IT WITH YOU, ANYWAY?

10:06.170 --> 10:07.694
-THERE'S A LOT AT STAKE HERE,

10:08.216 --> 10:09.870
AND I'M NOT GONNA
LET SOME WAVE JUNKIE

10:10.000 --> 10:11.785
WHO LIKES TO HANG OUT AND
BAG RAYS, BLOW IT FOR ME.

10:12.437 --> 10:13.961
[CHUCKLES]

10:14.570 --> 10:17.486
-OKAY, HERE'S HOW WE'RE
GONNA HANDLE THINGS.

10:17.617 --> 10:20.358
I'LL MIND MY BUSINESS
AND STAY OUT OF YOUR WAY.

10:20.489 --> 10:22.143
AND YOU DAMN WELL
MIND YOUR OWN BUSINESS

10:22.273 --> 10:23.187
AND STAY OUT OF MINE.

10:29.237 --> 10:32.109
[MELODIC MELODY]
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

10:40.857 --> 10:42.642
-YOU GOTTA COME WITH ME, STEPH.

10:43.817 --> 10:45.601
IT WOULD BE THE
ADVENTURE OF A LIFETIME.

10:45.732 --> 10:47.081
-I WANT TO, RILEY.

10:47.211 --> 10:48.604
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW MUCH
I WANNA COME WITH YOU.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.301
-WELL, THEN WHAT'S
STOPPING YOU?

10:50.432 --> 10:53.696
-NOTHING. IT'S JUST,
I DON'T KNOW.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.829
IT JUST SEEMS LIKE SUCH
A BIG COMMITMENT, YOU KNOW?

10:55.959 --> 10:58.353
TO LEAVE EVERYTHING AND
SAIL AROUND THE WORLD.

10:58.483 --> 11:01.573
-LOOK, IF YOU HATE IT,
IF AT ANY TIME YOU HATE IT,

11:01.704 --> 11:03.488
WE'LL FIND AN AIRPORT
AND YOU CAN FLY HOME.

11:04.098 --> 11:06.317
-I WON'T HATE IT. I'LL LOVE IT.

11:08.450 --> 11:09.799
-BUT WILL YOU LOVE ME--

11:09.930 --> 11:11.366
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE
WORRIED ABOUT, ISN'T IT?

11:18.678 --> 11:19.853
I LOVE YOU.

11:22.638 --> 11:23.683
-I KNOW.

11:27.121 --> 11:29.253
I JUST NEED MORE TIME
TO DECIDE, RILEY.

11:29.384 --> 11:30.864
-WELL, THERE'S NOT
MUCH TIME, STEPH.

11:30.994 --> 11:32.517
IF WE'RE GONNA KEEP IT
AHEAD OF THE WEATHER,

11:32.648 --> 11:34.258
WE GOTTA BE OUT OF HERE
NO LATER THAN SATURDAY.

11:34.389 --> 11:35.390
[SIGHS]

11:35.520 --> 11:36.608
-WHY IS IT I CAN MAKE DECISIONS

11:36.739 --> 11:37.784
ABOUT EVERYTHING ELSE SO EASILY,

11:37.914 --> 11:39.002
BUT WHEN IT COMES TO MY LIFE--

11:44.094 --> 11:45.574
-WHY DON'T YOU LET ME
HELP YOU DECIDE?

11:45.705 --> 11:48.185
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYS]

11:58.630 --> 11:59.675
-THERE SHE IS.

12:03.331 --> 12:06.203
[CAMERA LENS CLICKS]

12:10.294 --> 12:12.253
[CAMERA LENS CLICKS]

12:24.395 --> 12:27.007
-SHE'LL SWIM OUT TO THAT
BUOY, BE BACK IN 20 MINUTES.

12:28.182 --> 12:29.487
-20 MINUTES, YOU'RE SURE?

12:32.360 --> 12:33.491
YOU'D BETTER BE RIGHT.

12:34.754 --> 12:37.452
THIS IS SAM, BASE 1.
TARGET IS OFF THE PROPERTY.

12:37.582 --> 12:39.497
YOU HAVE 17 MINUTES. MOVE IN.

12:40.672 --> 12:42.022
-FRIENDS ON THE BLUFF

12:42.152 --> 12:43.327
DOING A LITTLE BREAKING
AND ENTERING, HUH?

12:44.415 --> 12:47.070
-THEY NEED TO PLANT
A LISTENING DEVICE ON HER PHONE.

12:47.984 --> 12:49.681
THERE ARE LIVES AT STAKE HERE.

12:50.813 --> 12:53.120
[GASPING]

12:58.212 --> 12:59.300
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

13:00.214 --> 13:01.693
-TO BAG SOME RAYS.

13:10.267 --> 13:11.965
-[GASPING] I'M CAUGHT!

13:12.095 --> 13:14.663
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

13:21.713 --> 13:24.804
-HELP! HELP! HELP!

13:24.934 --> 13:27.981
MY BOYFRIEND'S IN TROUBLE.
HE'S CAUGHT IN A RIPTIDE.

13:28.111 --> 13:31.811
HE'S BEEN DRINKING.
YOU'VE GOTTA HELP HIM!

13:34.291 --> 13:36.511
COME ON! WHAT ARE
YOU WAITING FOR?

13:36.641 --> 13:37.729
HE'S DROWNING!

13:43.953 --> 13:46.216
[GASPING]

13:47.783 --> 13:48.784
-THERE!

13:49.698 --> 13:51.874
[WAVES CRASHING]

13:55.922 --> 13:58.838
-HELP ME! [WHIMPERING LOUDLY]

14:05.627 --> 14:06.758
[GASPING]

14:08.282 --> 14:09.936
HELP ME! HELP ME!

14:11.067 --> 14:11.938
-HERE.

14:15.158 --> 14:16.203
-YOU OKAY?

14:16.333 --> 14:17.291
-I'M FINE, THANKS.
-OKAY.

14:18.335 --> 14:20.076
[LOUD GASPING]

14:20.816 --> 14:21.861
-TAKE IT EASY!

14:28.868 --> 14:29.956
[GROANING]

14:30.086 --> 14:31.174
[GASPING]

14:31.914 --> 14:35.744
[PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

14:45.972 --> 14:47.974
-I GOT YOU. MATT, MATT.

14:50.846 --> 14:51.847
-I GOT HIM.

14:51.978 --> 14:53.022
-I'M GOING AFTER MORGAN.

14:54.328 --> 14:56.025
[GASPING]

14:56.156 --> 14:59.289
[WAVES CRASH]

15:15.088 --> 15:16.611
[PEOPLE EXCLAIMING]

15:16.741 --> 15:18.918
-THANK YOU. ARE YOU OKAY?

15:19.048 --> 15:20.528
-EVERYTHING'S GONNA
BE ALL RIGHT, MA'AM.

15:20.658 --> 15:21.572
-OH, THANK YOU.

15:22.095 --> 15:24.097
ARNIE, I WAS SO WORRIED.

15:24.227 --> 15:26.447
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

15:30.581 --> 15:32.279
[COUGHS]

15:42.680 --> 15:44.030
-ATTAGIRL. ATTAGIRL.

15:45.031 --> 15:47.163
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.

15:48.077 --> 15:49.122
YOU OKAY?

15:50.645 --> 15:53.474
-I'M FINE, LEAVE ME
ALONE! I'M FINE, I'M FINE!

15:53.604 --> 15:55.128
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

15:55.258 --> 15:58.174
[PEOPLE TALKING
INDISTINCTLY IN BACKGROUND]

16:12.145 --> 16:13.973
-I SAVE HER LIFE, BUT I
DON'T EVEN GET A THANK YOU.

16:14.103 --> 16:15.539
-YOU'RE LUCKY, TRUST ME.

16:16.323 --> 16:18.325
TOWEL?
-YEAH.

16:28.291 --> 16:29.989
-COLD DRINK. THE SUN IS HOT.

16:30.902 --> 16:33.383
-THANK YOU. THAT'S VERY NICE.

16:34.863 --> 16:36.821
I APPRECIATE EVERYTHING
YOU'RE DOING, GRETA.

16:37.735 --> 16:40.521
IN FACT, IF I WASN'T
A LIFEGUARD, I'D LOVE IT.

16:41.870 --> 16:43.045
BUT I'M GONNA GET IN TROUBLE.

16:44.568 --> 16:45.961
-THE SHADE IS BETTER.

16:46.092 --> 16:47.876
-GRETA, YOU REALLY
DON'T HAVE TO DO THIS.

16:48.007 --> 16:48.877
-YES, I DO.

16:49.008 --> 16:50.009
-NO, YOU DON'T.

16:52.707 --> 16:55.231
I, UH... I GOTTA GO
BACK TO MY TOWER.

16:55.362 --> 16:56.189
-I WILL COME WITH YOU.

17:02.978 --> 17:04.414
[DOOR SLAMS]

17:04.545 --> 17:06.460
-GRETA, GRETA! GRETA,
WAIT, WAIT, PLEASE!

17:07.852 --> 17:09.202
I WANNA TALK TO YOU.

17:11.987 --> 17:14.990
LOOK, YOU COME FROM
A SMALL VILLAGE,

17:15.121 --> 17:17.252
AND I KNOW THINGS
ARE DIFFERENT THERE.

17:17.384 --> 17:21.344
AND I DON'T MEAN TO HURT YOUR
FEELINGS, BUT IT'S THE '90S.

17:22.214 --> 17:25.653
THINGS HAVE CHANGED.
MEN AND WOMEN HAVE CHANGED.

17:26.219 --> 17:27.481
DO YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN?

17:29.526 --> 17:31.659
IT'S NOT RIGHT FOR YOU
TO BE A MAN'S SLAVE.

17:32.399 --> 17:34.575
-IF A WOMAN SAVED ME,
IF YOU DID,

17:34.705 --> 17:35.793
I WOULD DO THE SAME FOR YOU.

17:36.403 --> 17:38.144
-YOU SHOULDN'T DO IT
FOR A MAN OR A WOMAN.

17:38.274 --> 17:41.582
-I DON'T DO IT FOR THE MAN,
I DON'T DO IT FOR THE WOMAN.

